Brazil Government Sees Economy Growing Less Than 4% This Year, Folha Says

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-08-26T09:17:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/brazil-government-sees-economy-growing-less-than-4-this-year-folha-says.html
Brazil ’s government is internally
forecasting that the country’s economy will grow by 3.7 percent
this year, below the 4 percent figure provided this week by
Finance Minister  Guido Mantega , Folha de S. Paulo reported,
without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
